  <h2 class="sec-title" id="weatherTitle">When to Visit <em>Ladakh</em></h2>
  <p class="sec-body" id="weatherNote" style="margin-bottom:0">Ladakh has extreme seasons — from -30°C in winter to 33°C in summer. The main tourist season is May to September when roads are open, lakes are accessible and the landscape is at its most dramatic. The Manali-Leh highway opens around May; the Srinagar-Leh highway opens earlier. Winter (November-February) is for the Chadar Trek and extraordinary stargazing — but extreme cold and road closures require serious preparation.</p>
